  "failure_cases": [
    "Very long sequences (O(n^2) attention complexity)",
    "Tasks requiring fine-grained positional information beyond sinusoidal encoding",
    "Small datasets where the model may overfit without careful regularization"
  ],
  "key_findings": [
    "The Transformer is the first sequence transduction model based entirely on attention, replacing recurrent and convolutional layers",
    "Achieves 28.4 BLEU on WMT 2014 En-De (new SOTA) at a fraction of training cost of previous methods",
    "Multi-head attention is critical but requires sufficient per-head dimensionality",
    "Training parallelism from removing recurrence leads to dramatically faster training",
    "Regularization (dropout, label smoothing) is essential for good performance"
  ]
